        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Mid-Semester Exam Performance",
          "Passed (1) vs Failed (0)",
          "134 CS1 Students, 140 CS2 Students",
          "Computer Science Courses",
          "Student Characteristics, \nPrior Academic History, LMS logs, Submission Records",
          "[Distance, CAO Points, MAth LC, Avg. Grade, Exam Course Year, Results Wx, Cumulative Wx, Lab Attendance Wx, Time Wx, Lab Access Wx, Hour Access Wx, Checking Wx, On/of Campus Wx, Week(end) Wx]",
          "Every Week",
          "Demographic variables were not considered as not to perpetuate biases stemming from previous cohorts.\n\nEvery week, a new set of behavioral features was extracted. Thus, model at week 5 includes all features for Model in Week 4 and the features that are specific for week 5. \n\n",
          "kNN, Decision Tree, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, Linear SVM, Gaussian SVM",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "Fail\n{F1-Score: 0.7450 - kNN, Precision: 0.7285 - Logistic Regression, Recall: 0.9479 - Gaussian SVM}\n\nPass\n{F1-Score: 0.0.6332 - DT, Precision: 0.7292 - RF, Recall: 06737 - RF}",
          "Authors create multiple models, one per course. For this paper the only published results are from a CS2 Course.\n\nA prediction is done every week. Ideal model was found to be kNN between Week 5 and Week 6.\n\nAuthors reach out to learners flagged as at-risk to provide some addtional feedback.",
          "Data is publsiuehd for a single course. \n\nDoes not explore potential features extracted from additional sources such as videos or speech.\n\nSmall dataset."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    },
    {
      "block_id": "1e24750c-f3ba-800e-b8dc-c1c19f64140c",
