        [
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Content-Based Filtering",
          "Computer Programming Recommendations",
          "133 CS2 students",
          "1 CS2 Course",
          "Programming submissions",
          "Recommendations are constructed based on a knowledge graph based on professor’s notion of important concepts.",
          "-",
          "The recommendations are a part of intervention.\n\nAt the end of each week, the system sends an e-mail notification to students with their progress and, if learner failed at submission.",
          "Most similar successful submission from top student.",
          "{% of Corrected Suggestions: 0.1160, Differential improvement for Opting-in: 0.1605}",
          "Participation in the intervention work was considered optional - After taking first exam, learners were offered the chance of receiving interventions vs not receiving them.\n\nAuthors measured “improvement” between students who opted in vs students who opted out:  All students performed badly on second exam but the decrease for students who opted-in was, at least, smaller.\n\nPositive feedback for interventions.",
          "Interventions are aimed for students flagged as likely to fail → Vulnerable to Misclassifications.\n\nRequires more data for better recommendations."
        ]
      ],
